			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Based in downtown Portland, Oregon, iovation is a market leader in web fraud prevention.&nbsp; We were recently named one of Portland&rsquo;s 100 fastest growing private companies.&nbsp;Customers around the world use our SaaS-based ReputationManager 360 service including leading banks and financial services companies, retailers, and MMO gaming providers.&nbsp; Building on constant product innovation and major partnerships, we continue to see strong growth.</p>
<p>
We are looking for a dynamic, self-motivated individual with experience and skills in the design and creation of technical and product-related content.&nbsp; This individual will own the design and development of product documentation, and develop copy for data sheets, white papers, and other productrelated material. Experience with multi-media content such as video is a plus but not required.</p>
<p>
In addition to re-designing, writing, and editing existing content, this person will work closely with the product, engineering and marketing teams to design and develop documentation and other product for all newly developed product features.&nbsp; The ideal candidate will have skills in technical&nbsp;writing, bring a strong design perspective, and be an expert in planning and delivering key material to support our&nbsp;sales and customers.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities<br />
&bull; Create, develop and manage content for all iovation products<br />
&bull; Edit and layout all product documentation<br />
&bull; Contribute content to data sheets, white papers and other marketing collateral<br />
&bull; Establish and maintain a consistent look and feel throughout all documentation and material<br />
&bull; Evaluate current content for gaps and opportunities for improvement<br />
&bull; Work with a cross-departmental team, maintain and develop the master product content calendar<br />
&bull; Keep current with emerging communication technologies including online/web and video<br />
&bull; Work cooperatively with key team members, clients&nbsp;and vendors</p>
<p>
Required Skills<br />
&bull; Exceptional communication and organizational skills<br />
&bull; Experience with software products and software<br />
documentation and marketing.&nbsp; Experience with enterprise software a plus<br />
&bull; Advanced knowledge of Adobe Creative Suite including InDesign<br />
&bull; Experience with HTML and content management systems such as Expression Engine, Joomla, Drupal, etc.<br />
&bull; Ability to manage multiple projects in a fast-paced,<br />
deadline-driven environment<br />
&bull; Proven ability to build consensus and work effectively within a cross-departmental team<br />
&bull; 3-5 years experience managing content and<br />
production for technically oriented products and product<br />
marketing related content<br />
&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in English, Journalism, Technical Writing or a related field<br />
&bull; Passion, Integrity and Energy!</p>
