			<description><![CDATA[<p>
iovation is in the business of making the Internet a safer place. We&#39;ve spent the last nine years developing award-winning technologies that now stop more than 100,000 fraudulent activities every day for hundreds of online businesses around the world.</p>
<p>
Position Profile: We are seeking an individual located in Europe, to play a critical role in providing iovation&#39;s clients with the best in professional support services.&nbsp; This individual will be responsible for supporting a group a clients to ensure they optimize the use of iovation&rsquo;s Device Reputation Authority.&nbsp; This includes training clients how to use the solution, analysis of activity for each client and across multiple clients&rsquo;, as well as quality interaction with clients and partners.</p>
<p>
As a Client Manager, you will work with assigned clients to:<br />
&bull; Develop an intimate knowledge of the clients&rsquo; risk management problems and issues, and assist them in maximizing the value of iovation&rsquo;s products.<br />
&bull; Develop relationships within clients&rsquo; risk management groups to enhance the perception of iovation as a valuable long term partner.<br />
&bull; Collect, analyze and interpret trend and risk data in order to make recommendations or develop solutions that enhance the value of iovation to the clients.<br />
&bull; Provide regular reports and analyses to customers about the impact and value of iovation&rsquo;s products on their business.<br />
&bull; Provide feedback to various groups within iovation that will assist in evolving the products and services, support sales efforts, and enhance client services&rsquo; delivery of services and best practices.<br />
&bull; Develop and maintain quality communications with all levels of staff and customers.<br />
&bull; Collaborate with others on the development of user manuals, training materials, and other materials as needed.<br />
&bull; Train each client to ensure they understand how to effectively use iovation&rsquo;s products and fraud management systems<br />
&bull; As required, participate in onsite visits with clients</p>
<p>
As a Client Manager, you will work with the sales team on assigned prospects to:<br />
&bull; Present product demos<br />
&bull; Participate in business use case discussions<br />
&bull; Lead strategic implementation discussions&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Deliver strategic plans for trials and full integrations</p>
<p>
For success in this role, you will possess:<br />
&bull; BA/BS degree in math, statistics, economics, business, finance or liberal arts.<br />
&bull; 3-5 years of client management experience.<br />
&bull; Excellent verbal and written communication skills and listening skills.<br />
&bull; Strong analytical and math skills.<br />
&bull; Strong problem solving skills.<br />
&bull; Skilled at proactively identifying opportunities and challenges, and developing solutions to address these.<br />
&bull; Strong customer-service orientation and relationship-building skills.<br />
&bull; Flexibility on working hours in order to accommodate special meeting requests, trainings, demonstrations for clients in different time zones.<br />
&bull; Self-starter with a &ldquo;Can Do&rdquo; attitude. Able to work effectively as a remote team member.<br />
&bull; Ability to prioritize and handle multiple tasks in a demanding work environment.<br />
&bull; Advanced skills with MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook.<br />
&bull; Some travel will be required.</p>
<p>
Extra consideration will be given to candidates with the following:<br />
&bull; Fraud Management or Risk Management experience<br />
&bull; Experience in the Financial Services industry<br />
&bull; Experience with iovation&rsquo;s product and services<br />
&bull; In addition to speaking English, fluency in one or more of the following: French, German or Spanish<br />
&nbsp;</p>
